<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="in-place">in place</h1>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.<strong>在适当的位置；适当的；准备妥当：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The ropes hold you in place so that you don’t fall. 
绳子会把你固定在适当的位置，这样你就不会掉下去。</p><footer>2008 安徽</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>After the dinner, an expression of thanks to the host would be in place. 
饭后向主人道声谢是比较合适的。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The service could be in place by the end of the year.
这项服务将于年底准备就绪。</p></div></div>